This paper is about a type inference system for a functional programming language, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the design space of local type inference, which could be relevant to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper mentions System F, a typed lambda calculus, which is related to the type theory (cs.TY) sub-category. The paper also discusses the implementation and error messages, which could be relevant to the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions curried applications, which could be relevant to the formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) sub-category.
